# Metrics

This document enumerates the metrics collected by this project using the [Glean SDK](https://mozilla.github.io/glean/book/index.html).
This project may depend on other projects which also collect metrics.
This means you might have to go searching through the dependency tree to get a full picture of everything collected by this project.

# Pings

- [breach-resolution](#breach-resolution)
- [deletion-request](#deletion-request)
- [events](#events)
- [user-journey](#user-journey)

## breach-resolution

A custom ping containing metrics regarding breach resolution.


This ping includes the [client id](https://mozilla.github.io/glean/book/user/pings/index.html#the-client_info-section).

**Data reviews for this ping:**

- <https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/TODO>

**Bugs related to this ping:**

- <https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/TODO>

All Glean pings contain built-in metrics in the [`ping_info`](https://mozilla.github.io/glean/book/user/pings/index.html#the-ping_info-section) and [`client_info`](https://mozilla.github.io/glean/book/user/pings/index.html#the-client_info-section) sections.

In addition to those built-in metrics, the following metrics are added to the ping:

| Name | Type | Description | Data reviews | Extras | Expiration | [Data Sensitivity](https://wiki.mozilla.org/Firefox/Data_Collection) |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| breaches.resolve |[datetime](https://mozilla.github.io/glean/book/user/metrics/datetime.html) |Sent each time a user resolves a non-password breach.  |[Review 1](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/TODO)||never |1 |
| breaches.resolve_password |[datetime](https://mozilla.github.io/glean/book/user/metrics/datetime.html) |Sent each time a user resolves a password breach.  |[Review 1](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/TODO)||never |1 |
| monitor.id |[uuid](https://mozilla.github.io/glean/book/user/metrics/uuid.html) |The id of the current Monitor user client. This is generated by the Monitor server. A value of 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000 indicates a test payload. A value of 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111 indicates that the Rally id was not found or properly set.  |[Review 1](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/TODO)||never | |
